      • downloadBegin

        public void downloadBegin()
        Indicates that the file download portion of the process has begun. Download processes typically have file download portions as well as other discovery and/or update portions. This method indicates that the bytes downloaded should be displayed to the user in some form.
        See Also:
        downloadEnd()

      • fileBegin

        public FileProgress fileBegin​(java.lang.String source,
                              java.nio.file.Path target,
                              long sizeInBytes)
        Display the beginning of a file download.
        Parameters:
        source - a String containing the source location in a form suitable for display.
        target - the Path where the file should be written
        sizeInBytes - the size of the file in bytes
        Returns:
        a FileProgress that should be used to indicate the progress of this particular file download
